		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=2549"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
 
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=2549')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=6047&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Yes+it%27s+true%2C+Enchanters+have+95%25+our+mana+regen"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> I limited this to Enchanters not to pick on them per se, but to highlight a class for comparison that will *always* have KEI. They have the spell, after all.</P><P>Let's get to the meat. I left out Flowing Thought items, since they apply to both classes. Here are the mana regen rates of an Enchanter versus a Necro:</P><P>-------------------------------------<BR>Enchanter:</P><P>14(KEI) + 25(Med) /tick = 39 mana/tick</P><P>Necromancer:</P><P>35(Arch Lich) + 25(Med) /tick, + 66%(PvP DMG Reduction) of -53hp/tick(HP loss from Arch Lich) = 60 mana/tick + (-35hp/tick)<BR>---------------------------------------</P><P>Difference between the two mana-wise: 21mana/tick, or to put it comparatively, the enchanter has 65% the mana regen of a necro.</P><P>This is deceptive.</P><P>Each tick the necro loses 35hp to Arch Lich. To regain that hp, they must use lifetaps. Let us use the efficiency of Touch of Night (level 59 lifetap, costing 405mana to heal 720hp, and figure out the REAL mana regen rate of the necromancer:</P><P>Touch of night = 0.56 mana per HP healed.</P><P>Therefore, using that math, to heal the 35hp the necro loses each tick, they must spend an additional 19 mana per tick on lifetaps.</P><P>Let us then take that mana/tick and subtract it from the original amount of 60, to give us the necro's real mana regen rate:</P><P>41 mana/tick.</P><P>The enchanter's is, let me remind you, 39mana/tick, with no hp loss. Thus, the mana regen of the Enchanter is 95% that of the necro, effectively. This applies to ANY pure caster class with KEI.</P><P>Well, what's a necro to do? Is that extra TWO mana per tick worth eating away at your HP for? Nah not really. Might as well just take a KEI. Our spells have horrible dmg/hp to mana ratios to make up for our supposedly insane mana regen, but really, our mana regen is not so insane after all. Not by a long shot.</P><P>First our twitch lines are made useless by Modrod2, now our lich line is proving to be under attack from KEI. My proposed solution? KEI must be made to stack with Arch Lich. Period. Whatever justification for the non-stacking was, it's moot now.</P><P>Dolalin Bonewielder<BR>Warlock of The Shadow Order<BR>Lanys T`Vyl</P><P>Edited by - Dolalin on 07/15/2002  06:14:35</font></td>

      </tr>

