         Yes lifetaps do damage, but at what cost? 720dmg for 405 mana IS A HORRIBLE RATIO!!</P><P>Let's figure you've got a KEI and are regening mana at 39/tick sitting, or standing if you have a horse (since you can't lich on a horse, but KEI works fine...). </P><P>You throw Pyrocruor on the mob. That's 1998dmg for 400 mana. 5.0 dmg/mana ratio. ToN is 1.7 dmg/mana. Do you see the difference there?</P><P>If you have KEI, YOU DON'T NEED TO CAST LIFETAPS! THEY ARE A WASTE OF MANA!</P><P>Throw Funeral Pyre on the mob for a 4.8dmg/mana ratio, and Pyrocruor for a 5.0 dmg/mana ratio, and you're doing an average of 4.9 damage per mana between the two spells. You're also doing 60 DPS, sustained, with no HP loss.</P><P>Throw Pyrocruor and Funeral Pyre on a mob using lich, and then ToN it back, and guess what? Your DPS may be higher, but your damage/mana ratio will be LOWER in the long run. ToN is a horrible ratio! You are WASTING MANA KEEPING YOURSELF HEALED!</P><P>4.8 + 5.0 + 1.7 / 3, guess what, you're operating at a 3.83 average DMG/mana ratio!! Think about that, you're 25% less efficient than if you'd just gotten KEI!</P><P>Numbers don't lie!</P><P>Necro with KEI = 4.9 dmg/mana ratio overall<BR>Necro with Lich = 3.83 dmg/mana ratio overall</P><P>Dolalin Bonewielder<BR>Warlock of The Shadow Order<BR>Lanys T`Vyl</P><P>Edited by - Dolalin on 07/15/2002  07:11:01<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
